channel.title: Need help with starting up server
channel.description:
Hi i have a belkin model F5D9230-4v2
idk how to portfoward it
I followeed the guide and everything
i ahve the ports and ip
But when i host server it doesnt work
Yes i have no-ip running while i press run server
i have compiled many times
HELP??
do i have to restart router??

item.title: Need help with starting up server
item.dc:creator: @kingofnone kingofnone
item.description:
@kingofnone wrote:

yeah your default gateway is youre router… pretty much
use that ip as a url normally 192.168.1.# in this case idk urs because i dont have your router
after you do that go to something called applications and gaming and add a port name
add the port range 43594 and then your pretty much good i may have missed a few things being as our routers and portforward screens are very different
